Unbelievable. I ordered $56 worth of food on seamless. The lady calls me and says they are out of whipped cream for the $9 slice of cake. I was like, OK, can you just throw in a scoop of vanilla ice cream, and she was like No, we charge for that. Then I said, ok, then just cancel the order. She asks, may I ask why? I said, you can't just throw in a scoop of ice cream? She says, hold on, let me talk to the manager. Immediately comes back and says, ok, we'll cancel it. It irked me, so I called back. The manager answered. I was like I just ordered, and you were out of whipped cream and wondered why you couldn't just replace it with a scoop of ice cream. He aggressively says, take it up with grub hub, we charge for that! I said, I ordered $56 worth of food, with a delivery charge of $5 and I'm tipping $8 for delivery, and you can't throw in a scoop of ice cream to replace something you are out of for the $9 slice of cake. Aggressively he says, WE CHARGE FOR THAT. That is simply bad business and gross. Out of principle you should steer clear of this place. And if that manager is reading this, he should be embarrassed.
